channel.title: Independent Study
channel.description:
All of this year I have independent study for computer science every day as one of my hours. The only thing I really need to do in this class is read an AP Java course book and take a test every once in a while, but I've already finished all of the chapters I'm going to be tested on. So now I'm bored as fuck all the time, and can't think of much to do in class. I've been trying to think of a good project to work on or maybe a useful library I could write, but not shit is coming to me.
I don't have access to the internet, but I do have Visual Studio 2005 and Netbeans on my computer. I'm allowed to copy files from my flash drive to the computer, and if I want to install something (and I have a good reason) my teacher will give me privileges so I can. Any suggestions? (Please nothing Runescape related)

item.dc:creator: @Weebs Weebs
item.description:
@Weebs wrote:

[quote=“la­wl, post:9, topic:243512”][quote author=Moparisthebest link=topic=319826.msg2534007#msg2534007 date=1226633356]
What about a SOCKS wrapper (like tsocks) that supports dns lookups over socks5 connections? (that way I won’t have to do it ;))
[/quote]
thats somewhat hard to do, if you hook connect(), as tsocks does, you wont have access to the hostname info, only the already resolved address in the sockaddr struct

i cant think of any way you could do that cleanly[/quote]

If I had any idea what SOCKS were, I’d probably consider it. Not to mention I suck butthole with C++.
